article.headline: Canisius 69, Loyola, Md. 67
article.story: BALTIMORE -- Julius Coles' go-ahead three-point play with 43 seconds left gave Canisius a 69-67 win over Loyola, Maryland on Monday night. Frank Turner led the Golden Griffins (8-18, 3-13 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference) with 23 points. Greg Logins finished with 19 points and Coles scored 16. Canisius held a 42-34 halftime lead, but the Greyhounds (11-17, 6-10) opened the second half with a 10-0 run to take a 44-42 lead. A 13-2 run later in the half pushed Loyola's lead to 59-48 with 7:45 remaining. With an eight-point deficit, Loyola broke out on an 11-0 run with less than three minutes left in the game, capped by Coles' three-point play to put Canisius up 68-65 with 43 seconds left. The Greyhounds had one final chance to tie, but Jamal Barney missed a jumper at the buzzer. Barney led the Greyhounds with 30 points and 11 rebounds.
